word_mean_info__list.difference: 着重指把过去的计划或意愿变成现实。
侧重成功地完成一件要做的事情，强调结果或影响。
侧重有意或无意地产生出好的或坏的，实际可见的效果。
用作动词意为“造成”，“产生”，用作名词强调由于影响而产生特殊效果。如：The effects of the medicine are very good.(药效很好。)
可作动词、名词，指对某人的思想行为、性格等产生影响。如：She was influenced by her middle school teachers.(她受中学时的老师影响。)
普通用词，含义广泛，侧重因某种原因所产生的最终结果，而不是眼前的结果。
指因某种原因直接产生的结果，着重持续稳定与其影响。
普通用词，多指事物经过一系列发展变化所导致的最终结局，而不是某种原因的直接结果。常可与result通用。
多指随某一事件引起的，必然或自然的不良结果，不强调直接的因果关系，而侧重事件发展的逻辑关系。

bilingual.source: Drawing has an amazing effect on children.'
Good food has a positive effect on your health.
bilingual.target: 好的食物对你的健康有积极影响。

bilingual.source: Finning would have an unexpected effect upon Peter Benchley.
bilingual.target: 割鳍对彼得·本奇利产生了意想不到的影响。

bilingual.source: What effect do the rhyming verses have on the rhythm of the poem?
bilingual.target: 押韵的诗句对诗的节奏有什么影响？

bilingual.source: The truth is that scent has a powerful effect on our thoughts and emotions.
bilingual.target: 事实是气味对我们的思想和情感有强大的影响。

bilingual.source: The drift of the North Pole won't have a big effect on anyone's daily life right now.
bilingual.target: 北极的漂移目前不会对任何人的日常生活产生重大影响。

bilingual.source: Smoking has a harmful effect on health.
bilingual.target: 吸烟对健康有不良影响。

bilingual.source: The moon has a significant effect on the tides.
bilingual.target: 月亮对潮汐有显著影响。

bilingual.source: Pollution has a harmful effect on the environment.
bilingual.target: 污染对环境造成了不良影响。

bilingual.source: The reforms had a lasting effect on the economy.
bilingual.target: 改革对经济产生了持久的影响。

yingyinNormal.en: I see. And did Hanna Schmitz acknowledge the effect she'd had on your life? She'd done much worse to other people.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我懂了。汉娜·施密茨明白自己对你一生的影响有多大吗？她对别人的影响坏得多。

yingyinNormal.en: You do not seem to understand the effect Mr Crawley's death has had on me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好像并不了解卡劳利先生的死对我造成了多大影响。

yingyinNormal.en: Of course, at the speed of trains and planes, the effect is minuscule.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当然，以火车与飞机的速度，对时间膨胀的影响是很微小的。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't control Congress. I'm trying to get two major initiatives off the ground and every move I make will have an effect.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不能控制国会，我想启动两项重要项目，我的每一步行动都将产生影响。

yingyinNormal.en: I thought it best to keep you separated. You've always had an odd effect on one another. No doubt due to how things ended for poor old Arnold.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得最好让你们分开，你们之间总是会奇怪地互相影响，因为可怜的阿诺德的结局，也难怪。

yingyinNormal.en: To see why moving faster through space affects passage of time, we need to go back to the 1880s, when two American scientists, Albert Michelson and Edward Morley, were trying to measure the effect of the Earth's movement around the Sun on the speed of light.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果想了解为什么加快在空间里的行驶速度会影响时间流逝的速度,我们得回到1880年,当时 两个美国科学家阿尔伯特?迈克尔逊 和 爱德华?莫雷尝试衡量地球绕太阳对光速有什么影响。

yingyinNormal.en: This is about reaching the age where we determine what's important. I am not afraid of my own mother. Why does she have this effect on people?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是关于我们变成熟，能自己决定什么最重要。我又不怕自己的亲妈。她为什么这么有影响力？

yingyinNormal.en: It does have a ripple effect. It does.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这确实是蝴蝶效应，确实是。

yingyinNormal.en: My hypotheses tend to have that effect.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的假设就是想有这种效果。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, sure, I see it now. The Doppler effect.
yingyinNormal.zh: 哦，我知道了，多普勒效应嘛。

yingyinNormal.en: This is where the placebo effect takes place.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是这些安慰剂发挥效果的关键点。

yingyinNormal.en: The placebo effect doesn't work for everyone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 显示荷尔蒙效应并不是对任何人都有效。

yingyinNormal.en: Depression's not a side effect of cancer. It's a side effect of dying, which is what was happening to me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 抑郁症不是癌症的并发症，而是将死的并发症。而我曾经差点就死了。

yingyinNormal.en: Next, we are going to steal, pause for effect, the moon!
yingyinNormal.zh: 接下来 我们要去偷的是，这时候停顿一下才给力，月球！

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, what's Sheldon supposed to be? Oh, he's the Doppler effect.
yingyinNormal.zh: 呃，谢尔顿穿的是什么？哦，他那是多普勒效应。

yingyinNormal.en: Very well, but, if you don't mind, I'd still like to pause for effect. Now…
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，但你不介意的话，为了戏剧化效果，我还是要停顿一下。现在嘛…

yingyinNormal.en: Traveling at 17,500 miles an hour, he experienced an effect known as time dilation, and one day the same effect might make significant time travel to the future commonplace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当时，他在太空时的行驶速度为每小时17500英里。他体验了一种名为"时间膨胀"的效应。而且，終一天 这种效应将会让穿越时空之时间更持久也变以家常便饭的事。

yingyinNormal.en: The booklets and the websites always list depression as a side effect of cancer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 传单和网页上写的都是抑郁症就像癌症的并发症。

yingyinNormal.en: And with that goal in mind, let me ask you a question. Do you believe in the placebo effect?
yingyinNormal.zh: 抱着这个目标，我要问你个问题，你相信安慰剂效应吗？

yingyinNormal.en: With this rate of tariff, I'm confident it'll have a mitigating effect on the anti-dumping cases.
yingyinNormal.zh: 目前这种关税率，我有信心这会对反倾销案例起到减震作用。

sense_info_list.en: a change which is a result or consequence of an action or other cause
sense_info_list.zh: 效应; 影响; 结果

examination_example.sentence: However, those correlations don't prove cause and <highlight>effect</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，这些相关性并不能证明因果关系。

examination_example.sentence: Such active research can have another <highlight>effect</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种积极的研究可能产生另一种效果。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>effect</highlight> is caused by the way we allocate our attention.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种效应是由我们分配注意力的方式引起的。

sense_info_list.en: used when you are stating what the facts of a situation are

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>effect</highlight>, the U.S. can import food or it can import the workers who pick it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，美国可以进口食物，也可以进口采摘食物的劳工。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>effect</highlight>, fewer federal funds today are going towards the agency's other work that affect the lives of all Americans.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，现在用于该机构其他工作的联邦资金越来越少，这些工作影响到所有美国人的生活。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>effect</highlight>, the White House claimed that it could invalidate any otherwise legitimate state law that it disagrees with.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 实际上，白宫声称，它可以使任何它不认可的合法州级法律失效。

sense_info_list.en: cause something to happen; bring about

examination_example.sentence: Though fast-fashion companies have made efforts to curb their impact on labor and the environment, Cline believes lasting change can only be <highlight>effected</highlight> by the customer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然一些快时尚公司都做出了努力来控制它们对劳动力和环境的影响，但是Cline认为只有消费者才能实现持久的改变。

表达"……影响了……"既可以说sth./sb. affect sth./sb.，也可以说sth./sb. have an effect on sth./sb. (……对……产生了影响)
例：Noise affects different people in different ways. 噪音对不同的人会产生不同的影响。

examination_example.sentence: Pasta does not have an adverse <highlight>effect</highlight> on body weigh outcomes when it is consumed as part of a healthy dietary pattern..
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为健康饮食模式的一部分，食用意大利面不会对体重产生不利影响。

examination_example.sentence: To measure the <highlight>effects</highlight> of Internet-based distractions during class, researchers evaluated 500 students taking an introductory psychology class at Michigan State University.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了衡量上课时网络干扰的影响，研究人员对密歇根州立大学 (Michigan State University) 上入门心理学课的500名学生进行了评估。

examination_example.sentence: Although these may not seem like large <highlight>effects</highlight>, the impact of early attention problems continued throughout the children's academic careers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然这些影响看似不大，但早期注意力问题的影响贯穿了孩子们的整个学习生涯。

examination_example.sentence: Likability by peers also had a modest <highlight>effect</highlight> on academic performance.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同伴的喜爱程度对学业成绩也有一定的影响。

examination_example.sentence: As countries continue setting goals of reducing emissions, greater steps need to be taken to have a noticeable <highlight>effect</highlight> on the surrounding environment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着各国继续设定减排目标，需要采取更多的措施才能对周围环境产生显著影响。

examination_example.sentence: Migrating birds affect ecosystems both at home and at their winter destinations, and disrupting the traditional routes could have unexpected side <highlight>effects</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 迁徙的鸟类会影响目前所在地及其冬季目的地的生态系统，破坏传统路线可能会带来意想不到的副作用。

examination_example.sentence: This, in turn, has a major <highlight>effect</highlight> on their diet, leading scientists to speculate that the ability to learn population-specific hunting methods could be driving the animals' genetic development.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这转而又会对其饮食习惯产生重大影响，该情况引发科学家猜测：学习种群特有狩猎方式的能力可能正推动虎鲸的基因进化。

examination_example.sentence: Dr. White said his team wanted to see whether living in greener urban areas had a lasting positive <highlight>effect</highlight> on people's sense of well-being or whether the <highlight>effect</highlight> also disappeared after a period of time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: White 博士说，他的团队想看看住在绿色城市地区是否对人们的幸福感具有持久的积极影响，或者这种影响在一段时间后是否也会消失。

examination_example.sentence: UK researchers found moving to a green space had a sustained positive <highlight>effect</highlight>, unlike pay rises or promotions, which only provided a short-term boost.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国研究人员发现，搬到有绿地的地方会带来持续的积极影响，这与升职加薪不同，后者只会带来短期的促进作用。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>effect</highlight> was unexpected.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 效果出乎意料。

examination_example.sentence: The regulation will come into full <highlight>effect</highlight> next month.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这项规定将于下月全面生效。

examination_example.sentence: It may yet be a selection <highlight>effect</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这可能还是一种选择效应。

examination_example.sentence: Marketing professors call it the decoy <highlight>effect</highlight>, which is certainly easier to remember.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 营销学教授称之为诱饵效应，这肯定更容易记住。

examination_example.sentence: The decoy <highlight>effect</highlight> works because of the way our brains assign value when making choices.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 诱饵效应之所以有效，是因为我们的大脑在做出选择时分配价值的方式。
